<doc id="8670" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=8670" title="Sir John Mills dies at 97">
<h1>Sir John Mills dies at 97</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=Sir%20John%20Mills%20dies%20at%2097&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 
Sir John Mills, &lt;a href="w%3AAcademy%20Award%20for%20Best%20Supporting%20Actor"&gt;Academy Award winner&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="w%3ABritish%20Academy%20of%20Film%20and%20Television%20Arts"&gt;BAFTA&lt;/a&gt; Fellow, and &lt;a href="w%3ADisney%20Legends"&gt;Disney Legend&lt;/a&gt;, has died, aged 97, at his home in Denham, &lt;a href="w%3ABuckinghamshire"&gt;Buckinghamshire&lt;/a&gt; after a short illness.

A funeral service for family and friends is scheduled to be held at St Mary's Church in Denham on Wednesday April 27.
<h2>Tributes</h2>
Various people have paid tribute to Sir John Mills and his 73 years as an actor in separate interviews with &lt;a href="w%3ABBC%20News"&gt;BBC News&lt;/a&gt;:
<ul>
BULLET::::- The actor Corin Redgrave called Sir John Mills a "great character actor", and described him as "a modest man who disguised his contribution".
BULLET::::- Fellow actor and long-time friend &lt;a href="w%3ARichard%20Attenborough"&gt;Lord Attenborough&lt;/a&gt; described Sir John Mills as "a hero of mine" who was "admired both by the general public and by the profession".
BULLET::::- Actor and producer Bryan Forbes commended Sir John Mills' "extraordinary courage" at never retiring, and remarked upon his humour saying "I had some of my best laughs with Johnnie".

</ul>
