<doc id="8685" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=8685" title="American who owns BenedictXVI.com wants &quot;one of those hats&quot;">
<h1>American who owns BenedictXVI.com wants &quot;one of those hats&quot;</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=American%20who%20owns%20BenedictXVI.com%20wants%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20those%20hats%26quot%3B&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 

Rogers Cadenhead, the &lt;a href="w%3AUnited%20States"&gt;American&lt;/a&gt; owner of BenedictXVI.com, has made a few requests in his blog. Mr. Cadenhead registered the valuable domain on April 1 along with ClementXV.com, InnocentXIV.com, LeoXIV.com, PaulVII.com and PiusXIII.com; all in anticipation of the recent &lt;a href="w%3APapal%20conclave%202005"&gt;Papal conclave 2005&lt;/a&gt;. 

After &lt;a href="w%3ACardinal%20Ratzinger"&gt;Cardinal Ratzinger's&lt;/a&gt; election as &lt;a href="w%3APope%20Benedict%20XVI"&gt;Pope Benedict XVI&lt;/a&gt;, international media swooped on the domain speculating that it may be owned by a pornographer or casino company. However amid the wild speculation, Mr. Cadenhead dismissed these and promised not to sell the domain to any such enterprises.

However today in a humorous manner the prolific computer guide writer posted on his blog a few requests, namely:

<ol>
BULLET::::1. Three days, two nights at the Vatican hotel they built for the conclave
BULLET::::2. &lt;a href="w%3AMitre"&gt;One of those hats&lt;/a&gt;
BULLET::::3. Complete absolution, no questions asked, for the third week of March 1987
BULLET::::4. A back-cover blurb from the Pope for the next edition of Movable Type 3 Bible Desktop Edition. But only if he uses the book to create his own weblog, and
BULLET::::5. World peace.

</ol>
However he was keen to stress that the requests are not demands and the whole thing was written in a witty humorous manner.

